Topic: PPDT (Picture Perception & Discussion Test) ⚠️ MOST IMPORTANT

👉 This is the elimination round
👉 Around 60–80% candidates get rejected here

If you clear this → You enter real SSB (4 days)

1️⃣ What is PPDT?

You will be shown 1 blurred picture for 30 seconds
Then you must:

1️⃣ Observe
2️⃣ Write a story (4 minutes)
3️⃣ Narrate your story
4️⃣ Group Discussion

🖼️ Example of PPDT Picture

👉 Image is usually:

Slightly unclear

Multiple characters

Some situation/problem

2️⃣ Story Writing Format (VERY IMPORTANT)

Follow this fixed structure 👇

🔹 1. Characters

Age

Gender

Mood (positive)

👉 Example: “A 20-year-old student Ravi, feeling determined…”

🔹 2. Past (What led to situation)

👉 Short background

🔹 3. Present (What is happening)

👉 Current situation in picture

🔹 4. Future (Solution – MOST IMPORTANT)

👉 Your hero solves the problem

🧠 GOLDEN RULE

👉 Your main character = YOU

Leader

Problem solver

Responsible

3️⃣ Example Story (Simple)

“A 20-year-old student Ravi noticed his friend injured during a football match. He quickly assessed the situation, provided first aid, and arranged transport to hospital. His timely action saved his friend and inspired others to stay calm in emergencies.”

4️⃣ Narration Tips (30–60 sec)

🎤 Speak clearly
🎤 Don’t rush
🎤 Maintain eye contact

Structure:

Character

Situation

Action

Result

5️⃣ Group Discussion (MOST CRITICAL)

👉 This is where many fail ❌

DO ✅

Speak 2–3 times

Support others

Be calm + logical

Help group reach one story

DON’T ❌

Shout

Fight

Dominate

Stay silent

👉 Officer = Team leader, not dictator

6️⃣ Common Mistakes

❌ Negative story (death, failure)
❌ Too many characters
❌ No clear solution
❌ Aggressive in discussion
❌ Not speaking at all

7️⃣ Practice Task (DO THIS NOW)

Look at any random image and write:

1️⃣ Character (age, mood)
2️⃣ Situation
3️⃣ Solution

⏱ Time limit: 4 minutes

🧠 PRO STRATEGY (SELECTION SECRET)

👉 Even if your story is average…
👉 You can still clear by:

Good narration

Positive attitude

Team behavior

💥 Discussion > Story

📊 Real Selection Insight
Factor	Importance
Story	30%
Narration	20%
Discussion	🔥 50%
